{ When White has three captures and only one of them leads to equality. } 8.
Bxc6+ { is more interesting. Then after: } 8... bxc6
{ White can try either capture: } 9. bxc3
{ Is a bit greedy. White intends to keep the extra pawn, but doing so leaves his king in the centre, surrounded by the enemy long-ranged pieces. Now I suggest the novelty: }
9... Qd5
{ Centralizes the queen and forces the White's knight to return to f3. } 10.
Nf3 Bh3
{ Black managed to keep the opponent's king in the middle and intends to castle and put both his rooks on the half-open d- and e-files. I would definitely prefer to be Black here ! For example:   10...O-O  is also possible, but the text is more aggressive and principled. }
11. Qb3 { is probably best when Black reaches a promising endgame after both }
11... Bg2
{ Or maybe even better:   11...O-O !?  12.Qxd5  cxd5  13.d4  Bd6  14.Bf4  Rab8  =∞ }
12. Qxd5 cxd5 13. Rg1 Bxf3 14. exf3 d4 *

