{ Fighting for the initiative !   13...c6 =  is the calmer way to equality. }
14. Qxc7 Re8
{ White is two pawns up, but has not yet developed his queenside. All his pieces are scattered and since Black will soon trade light-squared bishops his king is also in danger. Besides this move, Black can grab the initiative with the help of   14...Bg4 !?  Or   14...Bh3 !? }
15. d3 Bg4
{ All in all, it is White who has to repel Black's active tries.   15...Bf5 !? }
16. Qxb7 Rad8 17. b3
{ Here a problem becomes obvious. White cannot develop his pieces with:   17.Bd2  due to  e4  18.Bxe4  Rxe4 !  and mate comes next on f3. }
