1. c4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Nf3 Nc6 4. g3 d5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. Bg2 Bc5 7. O-O O-O 8.
d3 Re8 { Caruana remains true to his move. } 9. Bg5
{ Not a novelty, but a new try by the world champion. } 9... Nxc3
{ The simplest solution.  However, there is an argument for the preliminary   9...Nde7 !?  followed by either h7-h6 or f7-f6 in the future when White's provocation would not bring the desired result. }
10. bxc3 f6 11. Bc1 Be6 12. Bb2
{ Carlsen consistently prepares the advance of the d-pawn. But Black has many ways to meet it. }
12... Bb6 { Caruana pre-emptively moves away from the d4-pawn push. } 13. d4
{ A more ambitious try is   13.e4  but after  Bg4  White might not have time to advance the d-pawn at all. }
13... Bd5
{ But not   13...exd4  14.cxd4  Bc4  15.Re1  Ba5  16.Qc2 !  Ba6  17.Bc3  Bxc3  18.Qxc3  Rxe2  19.Rxe2  Bxe2  20.Qb3+  Kh8  21.Qxb7  ±  with big advantage for White  (Yermolinsky) }
14. Qc2
{ A critical moment in the game. After lenghty thought Caruana went for a concession and took on d4. Better was: }
14... e4 { to which Black probably feared: } 15. Nh4
{ After   15.Nd2  e3  Black is doing fine, or maybe more than fine  (Svidler) }
15... Na5
{ 15...e3  might be risky after  16.fxe3  Rxe3  17.Nf5   17.Rf2 !?  +=  17...Bxg2  18.Nxe3  Bxf1  19.Rxf1  although Yermolinsky likes Black, I am honestly afraid of the strong White centre }
16. Nf5
{ However, Black has a way out of this powerful idea. He can attack the center with: }
16... c5
{ White's idea is to meet   16...Nc4 ?!  Now  17.Ne3 !  Nxe3  18.fxe3  leads to a position which would have been clearly better for Black if he had the chance to back up the central pawn with f6-f5. Then White's bishop on g2 would be excluded from the game forever. Alas, there is no time for this because White will be better once he advances the c-pawn in the line:  c6  19.c4  += }
17. Ne3 Rc8 { and reach equal position after something like: } 18. Nxd5 Qxd5
19. dxc5 Bxc5 20. e3
{ Svidler  White's bishop pair is countered by Black's active pieces and a better pawn structure. }
*

