9... Bb4+ 10. Nd2 { after which Black had to play enterprisingly } 10... O-O
{ Now the easiest what was   10...Ba5  =+  defending the pawn. Gabriel,J  (2040)  - Semkov,S  (2445)  Berlin West, 1988  And this quickly brought fruits- }
11. Nxc7 { 11.Bxc7 ?  also loses as  Qe7  12.Bf4  g5  will trap it anyway. }
11... g5 12. Nxa8 gxf4
{ The knight is trapped on a8. It soon disappeared from the board. } 13. a3 Be7
14. Ne4 Be6 15. Qd2 d3 16. e3 fxe3 17. fxe3 Qxa8
{ And Black won after five more moves } 18. O-O Qd8 19. Rf4 Ne5 20. Raf1 Nc4
21. Qf2 Nfxe3 22. Rb1 d2
{ 0-1  (22)  Cox,J  (2350)  - Large,P  (2295)  London 1984 } *

