{ Let's wait again with the trade !  Especially when   11...axb5  12.axb5  Nd4  13.e3  Ne6  14.Qb3  ±  favours White.  The major alternative is }
12. e3 { when we can swap off a pair of knights } 12... Nxf3+
{ Or aim for more complex play with   12...Ne6  13.Qc2  Bd7  14.Rfd1  Re8  I actually like this one better, especially because  15.d4 ?  exd4  16.exd4  Nf5  doesn't give White any advantage. }
13. Qxf3 Re8 14. Qe2 Nf5 { slowly equalizing. } *

