9... O-O 10. b4 a6
{ Black wants to open the a-file for his rook and this should be good !  Although again there is a good alternative   10...Nd4 !? =  Or }
11. a4 Nd4 12. Nd2 c6 13. e3 Ne6 14. Nc4 Nd5
{ The position is approximately equal, but White plays somewhat inaccurately with }
15. Qc2 { To which: } 15... Nxc3 16. Qxc3 e4 17. d4 Ng5
{ led to a very pleasant position for the second player. His attacking perspectives on the kingside are obvious, and after the game continuation }
18. Ne5 Bh3 19. f4 exf3 20. Nxf3 Bxg2 21. Kxg2 Qd5 22. Rb2 Ne4
{ it seems that White offered his lower rated opponent a draw 1/2-1/2  (22)  Crosa Coll,M  (2449)  - Borges,L  (2303)  Sao Jose do Rio Preto 2006 }
