{ which intends to stop the d7-d5 advance but is a bit artificial. After some logical preparation d7-d5 will happen one way or another. }
5... O-O 6. Be2
{ Actually, pretty much every natural move equalizes here. This is how a solid French GM nicely unfolded his play against his more famous colleague }
6... d6 7. d3 a6 8. Bd2 Rb8
