{ NOTE We are playing positional system and look for ways to prevent any play the opponent might get. They are stronger on the queenside but if we block them there the centre and the other wing will be ours and we can have pleasant, one-sided game.  Or fianchetto the second bishop after   9...b6  10.O-O  Bb7  with equality after both  11.Nxd5  And   11.Bd2  Nce7  12.b4  Qd7  13.Rac1  Rac8  14.Qb1  c5  15.bxc5  Rxc5  which was equal and soon drawn in Savon,V  (2485)  - Farago,I  (2485)  Erevan  (Armenia)  1982  11...Qxd5  12.b4  Rac8  13.Rd1  Rfe8  14.Rb1  Nb8  15.Bb2  c5  ⇆  Sher,M  (2420)  - Shchekachev,A  (2570)  Paris 2005 In these lines Black made good use of the White's queen placement along the c-file. }
