1. c4 Nf6 2. Nc3 e5 3. Nf3 Nc6 4. d3 d5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. e3
{ would most likely transpose to the game Morozevich - Karjakin  (Reversed Scheveningen)  after  The main line is   6.e4  The only major move that has independent flavour. White is heading for the Classical Sicilian Reversed.  Whereas   6.g3  g6  7.Bg2  Nde7  would transpose to the reversed Dragon  (see chapter 2) }
