{ But it does not promise White anything after } 7... exd4 8. Nxd4 Bg7 9. Nxc6
{ 9.Bb5  is an empty blow after  O-O !  Then  10.Nxc6   10.Bxc6 ?!  Nxc3  11.bxc3  bxc6  ∓  10...Nxc3  11.Qxd8  Rxd8  12.Nxd8  Nxb5  Leaves White's knight in jeopardy. Luckily for White he can save it with a counter-sacrifice  13.O-O  Nd6  14.Rd1  Bf5  15.Rxd6  cxd6  16.Nxb7  but then White needs to work hard for equality, say  a5 !  17.a4  Ra6  18.Bd2  Bxb2  19.Re1  d5  20.Nxa5  Bc2  ∓ }
9... bxc6 10. Nxd5 Qxd5 11. Qxd5 cxd5
{ the strong bishop on the long diagonal secures Black some tiny edge, Savon,V  (2465)  - Yakovich,Y  (2530)  Belgorod 1991 }
