{ The main move and a very obvious one. We are ready to spoil Whites pawn structure and/or free the centre with the timely d7-d5 move. White has three different approaches now. The capture }
6. Nxc6
{ has innocuous reputation for a reason. It only reinforces Blacks centre and the second player can easily get rid of the doubled pawns. Moreover, the lack of the knight on f3 is often a major problem for White as the opponent can easily build a strong kingside attack. After  The only advantage of the move   6.Qd3  is that it prevents the doubling of Whites pawns. But it delays development and Black is more than fine after  O-O  7.a3  Ne5  8.Qg3  Bxc3+  9.Qxc3  d5  10.cxd5  Qxd5  ∓  Basyrov, E  (2001)  - Duzhakov,I  (2411)  St Petersburg 2016 }
