{ is a bit unpleasant, since after   7.Qc2  Bc5   7...Qd7  8.b3  O-O-O  9.h3  h5   9...Qe6  10.Bb2  Nd7 =  Christiansen,L  (2555)  - Kaidanov,G  (2580)  Parsippany 1996  8.h3  Qe7 }
7... Rb8 { we can no longer castle long. } 8. Qc2
{ Nevertheless, Black is doing fine after both } 8... Bd6
{ 8...Bc5  transposes to Murey,J  (2500)  - Lengyel,B  (2385)  Arnhem/ Amsterdam 1983   see move  5...Bf5 }
9. h3 h5 10. b3 h4 11. Bb2 Qe7 12. O-O-O Ba3 13. Be2 a6 14. Bxa3 Qxa3+ 15. Qb2
Qe7 16. Rhf1 b5 17. f3 exf3 18. Rxf3 Bg6 19. Rf4 Nd7 20. Rdf1 O-O
{ h5 could have been a problem for Black, but he found a good way to defend it, Rakhmanov,A  (2669)  - Korchmar,V  (2399)  Sochi 2017 }
