[Black "Carow, Johannes vs. Kulaots, Kaido"]
[Result "*"]

1. c4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Nf3 Nc6 4. d4
{ The most direct approach for White in the Four Knights variation. The first player tries to seize the initiative at once, but this should not work as we are not even behind in development. 'One of Botvinnik's favourites in the past, this line is not too fashionable today.'  (Marin) }
4... exd4 5. Nxd4 Bb4
{ The main move and a very obvious one. We are ready to ruin White's pawn structure and/or free the centre with a timely d5 push. White has three different approaches now. }
6. g3 { Often leads to positions similar to the Nimzo-Indian defense. } 6...
O-O 7. Bg2 { Now I recommend the immediate. } 7... Ne5
{ to force a concession while White is still underdeveloped.  Although the Nimzo-Indian set ups are also good after   7...Bxc3+  8.bxc3  Ne5  as in Kryvoruchko,Y  (2612)  -Karjakin, S  (2732)  Alushta 2008 }
8. Qb3 { To this White can defend with: } 8... Bc5
{ Retreat with a threat. White does not have time to castle. } 9. Be3
{ If   9.Nf3  Nxf3+  10.Bxf3  d6  is equal, say:  11.O-O  Re8  12.Bg5  h6  13.Bxf6  Qxf6  14.Ne4   14.Nd5  Qd8 =  14...Qe5  15.Nxc5  Qxc5 =  Dimitrov, R  (2341)  -Romanishin,O  (2528)  Bled 2008 }
9... Nfg4
{ and another threat of Nxe3. Of course White's can conjure up his own threats with }
10. Ne6
{ but this does not give him more than compensation for the pawn after: } 10...
fxe6 11. Bxc5 d6 12. h3
{ Worse is:   12.Bd4  Nc6  13.Bxc6  bxc6  when Black is a bit better. } 12...
dxc5 13. hxg4 { Or   13.Rd1  Qe7  14.hxg4  Nxg4 = } 13... Nxg4 14. Qc2
{ Naturally, White does not want to castle into a kingside attack   14.O-O ?  Qg5 }
14... g6 { Or   14...h6 = } 15. Ne4 e5
{ Forced play is over and Black is simply up a pawn, although it doesn't count for much yet as it is doubled, but who knows, maybe it will be a queen in the future ? In any case he has nothing to worry about from the opening. }
16. Bf3 Bf5 17. Rh4 Nf6 18. Rd1 Qe7 19. Qc1 Nxe4 20. Bxe4 c6 21. Qh6 Rf7 22.
Bxf5 gxf5 23. Rh5 Re8 24. Rd6 f4 25. Rg5+ Kh8 26. g4 e4 27. Rgg6 Qf8 28. Qxf8+
Rexf8 29. Rge6 Rg8 30. Rxe4 Rxg4 31. f3 Rg5 32. Rde6 Kg7 33. R6e5 Rxe5 34. Rxe5
Kg6 35. Re6+ Kf5 36. Rh6 Kg5 37. Re6 Kf5 38. Re8 h5 39. Rh8 Kg5 40. Rg8+ Kf6
41. Rh8 Kg6 42. Rg8+ Rg7 43. Rf8 Kg5 44. Rh8 Kh4 45. Kf2 Rd7 46. Ke1 Rd4 47.
Rh7 b5 48. cxb5 cxb5 49. Rxa7 Ra4 50. Rb7 b4 51. a3 bxa3 52. bxa3 Rxa3 53. Rc7
Rc3 54. Rf7 Kg5 55. Rg7+ Kf6 56. Rh7 Kg6 57. Rh8 Rc1+ 58. Kf2 Rd1 59. Rg8+ Kf6
60. Rf8+ Ke5 61. Re8+ Kf6 62. Rf8+ Kg5 63. Rg8+ Kh6 64. Rh8+ Kg6 65. Rg8+ Kf6 *

