1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Nc3 Nc6 4. d4 cxd4 5. Nxd4 g6 6. g3 Nf6
{ 6...Bg7  7.Nde2  Nf6  8.Bg2  O-O  9.O-O  Rb8  10.a4  a6  11.Re1  b5  12.axb5  axb5  13.Nd5   13.Bg5  b4  14.Nd5  13...Nd7  14.c3 }
7. Nde2 Bd7 8. Bg2 Qc8 9. h3 h5
{ 9...Bg7  10.g4  O-O  11.Ng3  intending g4-g5 looks good for White. } 10. b3
Bg7 11. Bb2 h4
{ A good practical chance !   11...O-O  looks too grim after  12.Rb1   12.Qd2 !  is even better-  b5  13.O-O-O  b4  14.Nd5  ±  12...a6  13.Nd5  Nxd5  14.exd5  Na5   14...Bxb2  15.Rxb2  Na5  16.Qd2  b6  17.g4   17.Nf4  17...hxg4   17...h4  18.hxg4 }
12. g4
{ Not:   12.Nd5 ?  hxg3  13.Nxf6+  Bxf6  14.Bxf6  gxf2+  15.Kxf2  exf6  16.Qxd6  Ne5  with advantage for Black. }
12... Nxg4 13. hxg4 Bxg4 14. f3
{ 14.Na4  Bxb2   14...Ne5  15.f4  h3  16.fxe5  hxg2  17.Rxh8+  Bxh8  18.Kf2  dxe5  15.Nxb2  h3  16.Qd2  Bxe2  17.Kxe2  Movsesian tried instead:   14.Rf1  h3  15.Bh1  Nd4  16.Qxd4  but the sacrifice should be unsound after  Bxd4  17.Nxd4  Qc5  Movsesian,S  (2635)  -Likavsky,T  (2514)  Czechia 2005   14.Qd2 ?  h3  15.Bf1  Bf3  ∓ }
14... h3 15. fxg4 Qxg4
{ Better was:   15...hxg2  16.Rxh8+  Bxh8  17.Qd3  Not   17.Kf2 ?  Qxg4  18.Qg1  Qh4+  19.Kxg2   19.Ng3  Be5  20.Qxg2  O-O-O  ∓  17...Qxg4  18.O-O-O  O-O-O   18...Be5  19.Nd5  Bxb2+  20.Kxb2  O-O-O  21.Rg1  Rh8  22.Nd4   18...Bxc3  has been played, and I like White after  19.Bxc3  f5  20.Qe3  O-O-O  21.Rg1  Jansa,V  (2409)  -Pulpan,J  (2382)  Czech Republic 2017  19.Nd5   19.Rg1  19...Bxb2+  20.Kxb2  Rh8  21.Nd4 }
16. Qd3
{ White is getting checkmated after:   16.Bf1 ??  Qh4+  17.Kd2  Bh6+  18.Kd3  Ne5+  19.Kd4  Qf2+ }
16... Qxg2
{ Black could have reverted to the line from above with:   16...hxg2  17.Rxh8+  Bxh8  18.O-O-O  O-O-O  19.Nd5 }
17. O-O-O h2
{ 17...O-O-O  loses the pawn after  18.Rdg1  Qf2  19.Rxh3  Bxc3  20.Bxc3   17...Qg5+  18.Kb1 }
