1. c4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. g3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. Bg2 Ne7
{ White can try attacking even earlier with: } 6. h4
{ Although this does not change the fact that there is nothing to attack on the kingside yet. After: }
6... Nbc6 { The only independent line is: } 7. d3
{ 7.Nf3  transposes to the previous line instead. } 7... Nf5 8. Bd2
{ Now White can spoil our pawn structure:   8.Bxc6+  bxc6  9.Nf3  f6  But this comes with a deer cost of a great bishop. Our plan is obvious- c6-c5, Nf5-d4 in a good moment, the light squared bishop goes on the long diagonal and we mate. }
8... Be7 9. Nf3
{ 9.Bxc6+  bxc6  10.Nf3  f6  transposes to the line from above. } 9... O-O
{ With excellent game for Black. } *

